      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f4afdbea_408b36b1",
        "filename": "go/mocks/GitStore.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 3,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-02T17:46:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s not in the gitstore package because I don\u0027t want to introduce the testify dependency into that package.\n\nIt\u0027s not in a subpackage because I imagine in a future with many mocks, it\u0027ll be kind of annoying to have a lot of subpackages named mocks. I can be convinced otherwise though.",
      "parentUuid": "53e4c344_15edf7dd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 3,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "123f82eff35a638fac2f1048e95d54bfb2938034",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "78de0756_e446516f",
        "filename": "go/mocks/GitStore.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 3,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-03T11:46:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I have a pretty strong preference for putting the mocks for a thing in the same package or a subpackage of the thing they mock.  I don\u0027t want to end up with a whole bunch of unrelated mocks sitting in the same package, especially at the top level.",
      "parentUuid": "f4afdbea_408b36b1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 3,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "123f82eff35a638fac2f1048e95d54bfb2938034",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b2b3f74d_87208473",
        "filename": "go/vcsinfo/bt_vcs/bt_vcs.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 117,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-02T17:06:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not sure how often we\u0027re doing Update(), but it seems to me that we could also pre-fetch details for all commits in range here.  My thinking is that it should be almost as fast to retrieve all of the commits as it is to retrieve a single one; pre-caching during Update() would help with latency in general.  We could optimize by only fetching details for those not already in the cache.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 117,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 117,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "123f82eff35a638fac2f1048e95d54bfb2938034",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
