    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3cfada8f_3cc7dddc",
        "filename": "go/vcsinfo/bt_vcs/bt_vcs.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 138,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-02T17:06:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is this really necessary?  BigTable should be very fast, and as implemented if multiple requests for the same commit come in at the same time, we\u0027ll make multiple requests to BigTable (and multiply write to the detailsCache).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 137,
        "startChar": 41,
        "endLine": 138,
        "endChar": 68
      },
      "revId": "123f82eff35a638fac2f1048e95d54bfb2938034",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2331aa78_e3f755dd",
        "filename": "go/vcsinfo/bt_vcs/bt_vcs.go",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 138,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-05-02T17:46:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "BT should be very fast, but if it\u0027s not I don\u0027t want to block read access to the cache if we have a BT flake and requests take multiple seconds.  I\u0027m not sure I can think of a way that doesn\u0027t block read access while we are waiting for big table and addresses your concern.",
      "parentUuid": "3cfada8f_3cc7dddc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 137,
        "startChar": 41,
        "endLine": 138,
        "endChar": 68
      },
      "revId": "123f82eff35a638fac2f1048e95d54bfb2938034",
